llm_column_description: The WebsiteUrl column stores the personal or professional website URLs associated with the users. It is a nullable text field, allowing for flexibility in user input.

gold_column_description: The user's location.
llm_column_description: The Location column in the users table stores the geographical location of the user. This information is represented as a string of text.

gold_column_description: Self-introduction of the user.
llm_column_description: The AboutMe column in the users table serves as a space for users to provide a brief personal description or biography. This can include details about their professional background, interests, or other relevant information.

gold_column_description: The number of times the user's profile has been viewed.
llm_column_description: The Views column in the users table primarily records the total number of views a user's profile has received.

gold_column_description: The number of upvotes received by the user.
llm_column_description: The UpVotes column in the users table represents the total number of upvotes received by a user. This is likely a reflection of the user's contributions or content quality.

gold_column_description: The number of downvotes received by the user.
llm_column_description: The DownVotes column in the users table records the total number of downvotes received by a user.

gold_column_description: The unique identifier for the user's account.
llm_column_description: The AccountId column in the users table appears to store a unique identifier for the account associated with each user. This could potentially be used to link users to their respective accounts or to differentiate between multiple accounts a single user might have.

gold_column_description: The age of the user.
llm_column_description: The Age column in the users table stores the age of the respective user.

gold_column_description: URL of the user's profile image.
llm_column_description: The ProfileImageUrl column stores the URL link to the profile image of the respective user.

gold_column_description: Unique identifier for each tag.
llm_column_description: The Id column serves as the primary key, uniquely identifying each record in the tags table. It is an integer data type and does not allow null values.

gold_column_description: The name of the tag.
llm_column_description: The TagName column stores the unique name or identifier for a specific tag. This name is used to categorize or label posts within the database.

gold_column_description: The number of posts that contain this tag.
llm_column_description: The Count column stores the total number of occurrences of a specific tag, as indicated by the TagName column.

gold_column_description: The ID of the post containing the excerpt for the tag.
llm_column_description: The ExcerptPostId column stores the unique identifier of a post that serves as an excerpt or summary for the corresponding tag. This post is likely used to provide a brief overview or context for the tag.

gold_column_description: The ID of the wiki post associated with the tag.
llm_column_description: The WikiPostId column stores the unique identifier of the post that serves as the wiki for the corresponding tag. This post contains detailed information about the tag.

gold_column_description: The unique identifier for each vote.
llm_column_description: The Id column serves as the primary key, uniquely identifying each record in the votes table.

gold_column_description: The identifier of the post that received the vote.
llm_column_description: The PostId column stores the unique identifier of the post associated with the respective vote record. It serves as a foreign key referencing the Id column in the posts table.

gold_column_description: The identifier for the type of vote.
llm_column_description: The VoteTypeId column stores the type of vote cast on a post, with each unique value representing a different type of vote.

gold_column_description: The date when the vote was created.

gold_column_description: The ID of the user who cast the vote.

gold_column_description: The amount of bounty associated with a vote.
llm_column_description: The BountyAmount column stores the amount of reputation points offered as a bounty for a specific post. It is associated with the UserId and PostId, indicating the user who offered the bounty and the post for which it was offered.

gold_column_description: This is the unique identifier for each comment.

gold_column_description: The unique identifier of the post associated with the comment.
llm_column_description: The PostId column serves as a foreign key, referencing the Id column in the posts table. It is used to establish a relationship between a comment and the post it is associated with.

gold_column_description: The rating score of the comment.
llm_column_description: The Score column represents the total number of upvotes minus the number of downvotes a comment has received. It serves as an indicator of the comment's overall approval or disapproval by users.

gold_column_description: The detailed content of the comment.
llm_column_description: The Text column in the comments table primarily stores the content of the comments made by users. It contains the textual information expressing the thoughts, opinions, or feedback related to the respective post.

gold_column_description: The ID of the user who posted the comment.

gold_column_description: The display name of the user who made the comment.
